text:
This was our last stop on our trip and I id I if cannot beleive I actually paid money to be here.
The property itself was nice.
The stay started off with our pool being broken so we moved rooms (they have 3) only to be kept awake all night by the couple next door going at it all night (the worst thing was that there is no sound proofing so it was as if they were in OUR room) 
The next morning we switched back to the original room as the pool had been fixed. 
If you do stay here DO NOT GET BRAKFAST INCLUDED because you will be paying however much extra it is per day for inedible food and nothing like pictured on the website or booking.com. 
We had arranged via email for 1 vegan meal per day (I am more than happy to have a piece of toast and some fruit. Super chilled) although each day it got worse and worse! 
And on the last day my toast was covered in strawberries and chocolate ice cream topping, my partners French toast was 3 pieces of cold toast smothered in both toppings with a side of maple syrup. 
(Refer to the pictures added) 
After checking out we organised for a driver to do an airport drop off, through the villa. 1 hour later we were still sitting there in the heat waiting and when we asked if they were still coming they said there wasn’t any transport available for us and that we should take a taxi (apparently you had to organise it two days before, which was not stated anywhere and we were told by the front desk that it would be fine on the day).
So almost 2 hours later they found a random driver to try and get us to the airport on time. 
All in all it was a shocking experience and when we tried to get our money back (after the first night) to change to a hotel they would not refund. So we were forced to stay there and be treated terribly. 
NEVER AGAIN! 
Also they said if we gave them a glowing review that they would give us complementary nights ect during our next stay with them, clearly not going to happen.
title: Worst Bali experience

text: My partner and I really enjoyed our stay at Manca Villa. The staff were so warm and accommodating from the start and made us feel so welcome. The staff were so nice and always had our best interest at heart, helping us when ever possible. The food surprised us how good it was and the service was amazing. The pool was great to have and we loved how open the bathroom area was. The only down fall was the mosquitos if you left the main door open (they loved me more than my partner). We thought it was a bad location at the start but it’s only a short walk to some great cafes and restaurants. We recommend bulls coffee for coffee lovers and buttermans for a cheap and but awesome breakfast and pastries! We had such a good experience at Manca, you can’t fault the staff and the service they gave us. The ladies at the front were always great to see each morning and also made my partner feel better about her self after a clothing mishap before going out for the night. (I need them all the time when this happens). Thank you so much Manca!
title: Highly recommend

text:
A villa that is smaller than expected, with obvious wear and tear in and around the villa. 

Pluses
The staff are helpful and tries their best, even when they don’t speak much English.
The walls of the villa are high enough, it’s private enough.
The bed was decently comfortable with 4 pillows 
Looks pretty on the pictures but looks really tired on closer look
Aircon works well for a room with high ceiling.
The greenery make the space looks cosy but lots of dead leaves and flowers that hasn’t been cleared.

Minuses
Day bed frames are chipped, worn out  while the day bed cushions are badly stained
The couch and pillows by the bed in the room have stains on them, bedsheets have stains, towels  are greyish and stained.
The bathroom wall is stained so badly some public restrooms are even cleaner looking.
The water pressure is weak, and hot water runs hot and cool.
The aircon on Low is noisy but that is easily solved when u turn the fan speed up
The dust on the lamp and mirrors shows it hasn’t really been cleaned.
The cupboards have a musty smell and there’s a dead lizard in the cupboard that hasn’t been cleaned out 
The design of all tabletops - kitchen counter, bathroom sink - are strangely high. I’m 168cm and it feels awkwardly high.
The hairdryer is the lowest powered travel hair dryer I’ve ever used. It usually takes me 3mins to dry my hair, this hairdryer took me 20mins and it’s still not dry!
There’s a resident lizard or two that’s  at least 10 inches long that hangs out every night which is freaky looking.
title: Booked based on good reviews but what a letdown

text:

Totally instagrammable. Bed is big, great pillows and weighted blanket. It faced a giant window towards the pool which gives great natural light. Kitchen comes with stove, microwave, basic cooking utensils. And the seating area is good for a casual WFH or breakfast.

Apparently they have a discounted price for decors and floating breakfast for y'all fancy couples. But for a solo traveller like me, this is def a luxurioud stay with a great discounted pandemic price. Recommended!

text:
I came here with my wife for a short honeymoon trip. This place was so romantic since the first step we came in this villa. Really fits for honeymooners and couples. Although it has semi-outdoor set bathroom adjoining the pool, our privacy was very well kept. Pool is nice for skinny dipping.
Location wise, Manca villa is very strategically located in the center of canggu Berawa beach area, only 5 mins drive to finns and nearby cafes. It is also not far away from Seminyak, so the location is a plus for me.
The staff was very kind and helpful. They politely guide us in the villa and offer the services. The minibar also came in with reasonable prices, unlike most hotel/villas.
Make sure you don’t come with a large car, especially when you self drive, because the alleyway is very narrow and the parking lot is very limited.
title: One of the best place to stay in Canggu

locations.name: Manca Villa Canggu by Ini VIe Hospitality

text:
First, let me just say that the staff here is amazing. They were so friendly, welcoming, and accommodating, and did everything they could to help when I couldn't find my passport upon arrival. They were always smiling, which was refreshing, and seems to be common in Bali :) 

The villa was perfection. It was completely spotless, everything smelled wonderful, and the linens were clean and made up nicely. They prepared the bed with rose petals and a welcome card, which I thought was a nice touch :) The decor was modern and very Bali-esque--lots of light, and pleasant colors. The pool was the perfect temperature, and there was plenty of hot water in the shower. The sink/bathtub area is absolutely beautiful, and is separated from the shower/toilet area and the bedroom by sliding barn doors.

We ordered a floating breakfast at the villa one on our last morning and it was delicious--the red velvet pancakes were my favorite, and I'm still dreaming about them now that I'm home, haha! 

The location is a little bit out of Canggu, but still within walking distance to shops & restaurants. It is also located nearby La Laguna & Finn's Beach Club, which are a couple of the best places in Canggu to watch the sunset (and Bali sunsets are definitely a sight to see!!)

I would rate my stay at Manca Villa a 10/10, and will definitely return here next time I'm in Bali!
title: Best place to stay around North Kuta!

text: Dit zijn hele mooie villa's voor 2 personen. Wij waren er half maart en we waren de eerste gasten. De Villa is splinternieuw en heel smaakvol ingericht. Alles wat je nodig hebt is er aanwezig, en meer dan dat. Heerlijk luxe allemaal. Wij hebben 2 villa's gehad die je aan elkaar kunt schakelen via een tussendeur. Erg gezellig. De staf is bijzonder vriendelijk en behulpzaam. In de buurt heb je veel leuke restaurantjes op korte loopafstand, er is een mooie yogastudio in de buurt en Canggu is een heerlijke trendy plaats. En ook nog eens dicht bij het strand.
title: Prachtige Villa in Canggu
